fields.descriptive_line: Set of 120 collector's cards commemorating the centenary of the modern Olympics
fields.physical_description: Set of 120 rectangular cards printed in colour with scenes from, reproductions of posters for and emblems of various Olympic Games and with texts about the history of the modern Olympics.
fields.title: Centennial Olympic Games Collection
fields.materials_techniques: Lithography, foil-blocking and varnishing on card
fields.location: Sackler Centre, tunnel entrance, case 1, shelf 2

fields.name: The Atlanta Committee for the Olympic Games

fields.public_access_description: This set of collector's cards was one of the official products licensed by The Atlanta Committee for the Olympic Games (ACOG). Atlanta hosted the games in 1996 and various commemorative souvenirs were produced to mark the centenary year of the modern Olympics.
fields.artist: The Atlanta Committee for the Olympic Games
